name: taking up space.
description: I found myself reading an article that immediately sent a reminder to my soul. I had seemed to forgotten that taking up space and being impactful+unashamed in my presence is something i deserve. Immediately i categorise as that queer-black-woman ; unfortunately society tends to not permit 'my kind' to fill spaces and take up room. We cant radiate our inherant divinity for this is too harsh and striking. But the article reminded me to take up space wonderfully. In the artwork i set out to convey this image!
